text: I get really emotional thinking about how far NMIXX have come. From their debut with O.O, when so many people misunderstood their concept and doubted them, to now, where everyone finally sees their talent and uniqueness. Watching them evolve and prove themselves has been such a heart wrecking experience. I’m genuinely proud of them and grateful for all the hardwork NMIXX does for us NSWERS. NMIXX mean so much to me, and I’ll always support them. NMIXX, you have been one of the best thing in my life. ily <3

author: @Zeldamaster93
text: Mark seriously fucked up the field puzzle. XD Just totally brute forced it. Well to explain this one, since I've been doing that with the other puzzles and they've been well received...It's all about how the scarecrows are looking at each other and where they're positioned. The first one had nothing in its hands and its arms were kind of raised like it was clapping, the second had dropped its sickle on the ground and was thus unburdened, the third was a female that looked like it was walking away from the corpse of the male in the center, the fourth was the female standing between a female staring at a male in affection, and the last one is obvious since it's the one that went off by itself and was all alone in the corner. This whole puzzle had some weird logic but overall I liked it. The Weeping Angel scarecrows were a nice, if very hated, touch.

author: @Mr_Thin_Man
text:
Hope Cory see's this 

here are the possible reason why the mirror shatters why Alone (The Girl) comes through

1. Loss of Idenitiy / Self-Reflection

- She is leaving behind a part of herself 
-She is crossing a point of no return
- Her reflection (or innocence) is broken in the process

2. Separation From Reality 

- It suggests the passage closes behind her, trapping her on the other side 
- She may now be in a different reality -alone, cot off, isolated 

3. Foreshadowing Betrayal or Transformation 

- A future change in Alone - maybeshe won't remain who she is 
- A future separation from Low - suggesting things won't end peacefully between them
